inn1.comm: full and outside off, Uthappa leans forward, opens the bat face and steers it to point.
Uthappa continues with the chennai mood. Fullish and on the middle stump line, driven between the bowler and the mid-on. India are up and away.
back of length, lands outside off, comes in a touch, Uthappa stands tall, runs it down to thirdman
from round the wickets, bangs it short of length, on the off stump line, Ganguly stands tall, gets on top of the bounce , pushes it to point
rapped on the pads. Going down though. Fullish, from round the stumps, on the leg and middle, Ganguly gets across, tries to flick, doesn't make contact
Just outside the off stump, full in length, nurdled to point
around the off stump, Ganguly pushes it out to Lara at cover. Lara makes the stop, rushes across to have a chat with the bowler
fuller, outside off, slanting away, driven to widish thirdman
ooh...almost dragged back to the stumps. It lands outside off stump, comes in a touch, Uthappa stabs at it and gets a inside edge

Huge huge shout for lbw. Looked pretty close. Fullish, on the middle stump line, Uthappa goes across the line and is rapped in front of the middle. Should have taken out middle and leg. Looked like dead duck but the umpire Saheba doesn't think so.   But hold on.... Virtual replay suggests that the ball would have missed leg stump!
short pitched one at the body, fended away to the on side
full and wide, width offered and Uthappa just flays it square through backward point.
what a reply! hits the deck short of length, outside the off stump, comes in a touch, Uthappa ends up playing inside the line and is beaten
back of length, slanting away, bit of width but Ganguly cuts it straight to point
tip and run. Ganguly pushes a length delivery towards extra cover and sets off with the stroke.
Uthappa makes Ganguly run. Pushed straight back to right of Smith who gets a touch and the ball rolls away to his right. Uthappa sees an opportunity for a run and calls Ganguly over
Bosh! Width offered outside off and Ganguly spanks it past point
this one slants away, run down to third man
fuller length, outside off, slashed away to widish third man. In the air but a controlled shot. That's the way he plays.
from round the stumps, trying to tuck up Ganguly, on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
short and outside off, slapped straight to point. Should have put taht one away. And Ganguly also thinks so.

almost a mix-up. Pushed to Samuels at cover and sets off, uthappa is not interested in collective suicide and remains at his position. Ganguly turns and rushes back and if the throw had hit the sticks he could have been in deep trouble
top-edged to fine leg! Bouncer on the middle and off stump line, Ganguly goes for a pull, is late on to the stroke and will get a boundary
super stop from Lendl Simmons. Ganguly turned a fullish delivery to right of square-leg where Simmons flung himself full length to make the stop
just outside off stump, Uthappa waits for it, opens the bat-face and dabs it to third man
on a length, around off , nudged to point
swing and a miss. 126 k outside off, short and slightly wide, Ganguly goes for a cut and is beaten as the ball keeps a tad low
fuller, outside off, pushed to cover.
good tight over. On the middle this time, Ganguly pushes it towards mid-on
Way down leg side. Uthappa tries to pull, misses, so does Ramdin.
Sehwagish! Short and outside off stump, Uthappa upper cuts it, short-arm jabs it over wide third man!
Wallop! What a shot! He just leans forward to slightly short of length delivery and just goes through with the line. That ball has disappeared over long-on
Revenge! kicks up from short of length, outside off stump, Uthappa stabs at it and ends up steering it straight to first slip.
outside off, left alone
again banged in short, outside off, Dravid jumps up, gets on top of the bounce and pushes it out to cover
drifts in on to the pads, tickled to square leg
fullish, outside off, Ganguly leans forward steers it to point
Ganguly pulls. Banged in short, on the leg and middle stump line, Ganguly pulls it  to long leg. Not much pace to really hurry the batsman
short of length, outside off, cut to deep point
beaten! Full in length, drifted in the air, lands outside off stump and shapes away a touch. Dravid pushes at it and the ball spats past the outside edge
on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
short of a good length delivery, coming in with the angle. Ganguly gets behind the line and defended it down

bowled from round the wicket, good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, again angled in. Ganguly makes room, gets his front-foot out of the way and punches it through the gap between mid-off and cover. Looked like a mistimed ball but the ball won the chase.
yorker on the stumps, excellent comeback delivery. Ganguly digs it out to mid-on
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Ganguly taps it away on the off side

take that! short and wide outside the off stump - enough room and that's where he likes it best! Cracking cut and the ball raced away through cover point. Second boundary of the over and Ganguly is on fire here. It's a no-ball as well so five runs added to the total
flicked away towards midwicket and they scamper through for a single
line and length delivery, Dravid gets behind the line and defends it down watchfully
steered down to gully and they sprint across for a single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Dravid stays back and taps it away towards cover
off the mark. clipped away off the pads and the Dravid gets it past the fielder at midwicket
defended outside the off stump
short but close to the off stump line, Ganguly leans back and finds the gap between point and gully, excellent placement
good length delivery outside the off stump and Dravid tamely plays it away towards cover. End of PowerPlay one.
good length delivery, again bowled from round the stumps and the ball was angled into Ganguly, who gets behind the line and defends it down on the off side
short of a good lenght and in the channel outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot

short and drifting down the leg side. Ganguly pulls and pulls WELL! ball files off the middle of the bat to the backward square leg fence. Just waited for the ball and lofted it over the fielder inside the circle. this is refreshing cricket from Dada.
worked away towards midwicket
driven straight to the fielder at cover point
defended back to the bowler, Dravid is struggling a bit here
full in length, outside off, steered to point
push and run. Nudged towards mid-off and he sets off for a run
Fullish, outside off,  Dravid gets on to the front foot, square-drives it past Simmons at point. He should have fielded that
Now Samuels fumbles a bit. Fullish outside off stump, driven just past cover, Samuels goes down on his left and should have stopped that
on the middle and leg, tucked to deep backward square leg
from round the stumps, Rayad Emrit hits the right spot. On a length, around off stump, pushed to cover point.
top-edge over the keeper. Ganguly tries to charge but Emirt drags back the length, Ganguly adjusts and tries to pull and gets a edge. Predetermined stroke
shuffles a bit across, and works a ball on the off stump line to the on side
fullish, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on
fuller, just outside off, dug out to cover
tossed up, outside off stump, turns in slightly, pushed back to the bowler
outside off, nudged towards cover
full, turns in from outside off, pushed to mid-on
on the middle and off, Dravid presses his left foot out, flicks it in front of his pad, to square leg
And again. Good tight over in progress
slightly short of length, on the middle, Dravid backs away, and forces it wide of mid-on
shot! short and outside off and cut past point. Easy pickings. Poor delivery.
now a no ball. Full in length, just outside off, pushed towards point. A good first over from Emrit and he is struggling a touch in the second.
better. Mediumpace on the middle stump, straight at the sticks, defended away on the front foot
lands on a length, just outside off, comes in a touch, Dravid works it to the on side.
drifts on to the pads, Dravid tries to flick it away, doesnt make contact and the ball rolls away off the pads
from round the stumps, on the pads, dabbed away to fine leg
short of length, on the middle stump, worked to midwicket. Drinks break is on.
floated outside leg, turns in, worked  to right of midwicket
tossed up on the off stump line, Dravid leans forward, drives past the bowler, Powell, from midon, gets across in time to make the stop.
Ganguly devices a plan to break the on side attack. He backs away to the leg stump, and lofts a ball on the leg stump, inside out, to widish long off.
100 up for India. Healthy run rate. flatter on the leg stump, Ganguly pushes it to extra cover
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket

Slap! Ganguly walks down the wicket, backs away to the leg stump , and just goes through the line. Over mid-off. Typical Ganguly shot. Does a lot in the ODIs. Predetermines the charge and manages to hold his head still and so even when the bowler drags the length, he is able to just punch through the line
way down the leg side.
on the middle and leg, tucked to square leg
Ganguly wants to get to his fifty with a single. Pats a ball on the off stump, close on the off side, and sets off, Dravid is not interested.
fullish, on the middle, driven straight to mid-on. Now Dravid sets off, after seeing Ganguly's initial steps down the track and is sent back

down the leg stump line, Ganguly flicks it and gets a fine tickle and goes to right of  Ramdin who gets his right glove on it but doesn't manage to hold on. Leg bye given but that went straight off the bat. Hmm...
turns in from outside off, defended on the front foot
Dravid takes charge. Tossed up on the off stump line and Dravid leans forward and lofts it over the bowler. Clean strike.
slightly short of length, on the off stump, cut to point
flat and full, on the middle,  worked to Lara at midwicket
just outside off, slightly short, cut to short third man
floated outside off, Dravid leans across, whips it to right of mid-on and will get a single
cuts back in from outside off stump, Dravid stabs at it and gets a inside edge on to the pads
whack! Dravid ringed the room service and Emrit served up a short and wide one, spanked past point
tip and run. short of length, around off stump, Dravid drops his wrists, taps the ball on the off and they run with the stroke. Over to Ganguly, on 49
That's his fifty!   62nd. Fullish, outside off stump and Ganguly leans forward, drives it through covers. Second fifty of the series. Dada is truly back.
again full, this time drifting on to the legs, worked to backward square leg
lovely slower ball. Fullish on the middle stump line, Ganguly charges down the track, spots the change in pace, changes tack, and pushes it back to the bowler
turns in from outside off, pushed to mid-on for a single
fired on the pads, tick;ed to square leg
pushed through quick. on the off stump, pushed to cover
Thwack! A strong legside field set and Ganguly backs away to the leg side and drills a fullish delivery on the leg and middle through cover
slightly short of length, on the middle, cut to Smith at cover who fumbles it and Ganguly will retain the strike
on a length, outside off stump, steered to point
on the stumps, defended to the on side
fuller, outside off stump and driven to Gayle at cover who fumbles this time. Quite a few mis-fields today
fullish, on the middle stump line, driven past mid-on. Just a mere push and he will get two for that
shifts his line to outside off, Ganguly opens the bat-face, runs it past point and by the time Bradshaw comes across from thirdman, they will get two
tossed up outside off, pushed past cover
lands on the leg stump, turns, Ganguly stays where he is, steers it to left of point
floated on the stumps, driven to long-on
full in length, driven towards long off
driven back to the bowler
short of length, on the middle stump line, Ganguly short arm jabs it to left of mid-on

Emrit continues with his steady stuff. Hits the right areas, not much pace but he is always there at the sticks. Bit of movement in and occasionally holds the line. This one comes back in a touch, from outside off, defended away
slightly fuller, on the off and middle, pushed to mid-on
much fuller, on the off and middle, Dravid drives it straight down the track, Emrit stretches out his right hand and makes a half-stop. Ouch. That must have hurt.
fullish, outside off, driven to deep cover
cuts his finger across the seam, comes in a touch from outside off, pushed to the on side.
on the middle and leg stump line, pushed to midwicket
on the leg stump line, worked to the on side
outside the leg stump, turned to square leg.
Ganguly decides to sweep to break the leg stump attack. Outside leg and he goes down on his knee
on the off stump, slightly short, Dravid goes back, punches it to the bowler
on the off and middle, Dravid tries to work it to on side, gets a leading edge, back to the bowler
Gayle also tries to operate on the leg stump line for Ganguly. Ends up drifting this one too much and wide called
floated outside leg stump, Ganguly tries to work it to on side, and the ball runs off fine, off the pads
on the middle stump line, Dravid leans forwad, whips it to wide long on
100 partnership is up. Again outside leg, swept fine
again outside leg, again he tries to sweep but doesn't make contact and the ball rolls away off the pads
almost cleaned up! slightly quicker, on the middle stump line, Ganguly tries to cut, late cut, and gets a inside edge to the leg side

Gone this time! Ganguly charges down the track, Gayle sticks to his outside legstump line and Ganguly meets thin air with his attempted heave, and Ramdin gathers the ball down leg side and whips off the bail.  Ganguly leaves the arena, cursing himself. The crowd are in more forgiving mood. They applaud his fifty.
On the off stump line, pushed to cover point
full in length, on leg and middle stump line, Dravid tries to whip it away to the on side and misses. It runs off the pads
fuller, outside off stump, Dravid throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge to third man
Tendulkar leans forward, covers the line, head over the ball and pushes a length-delivery to the off side. 31, 0, 60  so far in the series.
ah! the whip across the line is out. Typical Tendulkar shot, he leans forward to a fullish delivery, on the middle and whips it through midwicket.
slanted away, full in length, driven to Lara at cover
outside off stump, Tendulkar looks to whip it across, resists and just pushes it to the on side
on the off stump, worked to the on side
paddle swept fine. Predetermined of course.
on the off stump line, Slow through the air, Dravid drives to long on
bit of flight, pretty slow through the air, outside off stump, Tendulkar drives on the off side
tickled to square leg
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Tendulkar steps forward and drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off

classy! similar line and length, once again Tendulkar pushes forward and on this occasion he punched it straight back down the track, once past the bowler the ball just raced away to the long-off fence.

aggressive Tendulkar! Good length delivery, slanting across a bit. Tendulkar once again nicely comes on to the front-foot and drives it through the gap between the cover fielder, excellent piece of fielding in the deep saves one run. Seven runs in two balls
short of a good length delivery, angled across the right-hander and Dravid cuts it straight to the fielder at point
Bradshaw slightly off line, drifts on to the pads and Dravid tucks it away towards square leg. Early call and they scamper through for a single

good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Tendulkar was looking to push forward but the line and length was perfect and in the end all he could do was tap it away towards point. Good delivery to end the over
tossed up outside the off stump, Dravid leans forward and paddles it down to fine leg, takes on the fielder in the deep and comfortably comes back for the second
turning in, Dravid pushes forward and works it away towards midwicket
driven away towards point, no room for a single there
worked away with the spin to the midwicket region
quicker delivery and Dravid defends it down on the leg side
tickled to square leg
fullish, outside off, driven to mid-off
pre-determined paddle sweep. Just a run though for the risk of paddling a mdium pacer
on the off stump line, slanting away, pushed to off. Tendulkar goes across to have a chat with Dravid.
fullish, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on. Run rate has come down to 5.6 per over
pushes that one wide outside off stump, lost control at the point of release
just outside off, dabbed away to third man
Tendulkar tries to attack but drives straight to cover. Hit on the up and through the line. Looked good but doesn't reflect in the scorecard.
tossed up, low full toss in fact, Dravid is surprised, drives it to long off. The bottom-hand came of the handle
on the off and middle , Slow through the air, Tendulkar gets a leading edge to cover
again really slow , on the middle, not much pace to work with, turned to the on side
outside off, cut to backward point
outside off, flatter, Tendulkar leans forward, doesnt get room nor pace to work with, just turns to square leg
on the off stump line, full in length, Tendulkar, I got the impression, was beaten in the flight slightly but manages to whip it past square leg
Ramdin is standing up to the stumps. That last shot from Tendulkar in the previous over must be the reason. On the off stump, pushed to cover
short and wide, drilled to deep cover. Didn't place that one well.
just outside off, angling away, run down to thirdman. The most profitable odi shot.
catch it was the shout! short of length, outside off, cut to Dwayne Smith at point. Falls short of him. Again there was the room and the length to really punish the bowler but ....
tip and run. Pushed to short cover and they run with the stroke
nice pleasing drive but just a single to long off. Drinks break on.
slow, outside off stump, turns in, tries to work it to the on side, runs off the pads
get a tickle this time, to fine leg . Oops .. a leg bye signalled. I have to visit my eye doctor
slog sweep for four! He leans forward and sweeps, skies it up a bit but the placement was fine - in front of square and will get a boundary. on 49 now.
fifty up. flicked to fine leg.  50 in 77 balls. It was his 76th fifty.
on the off stump line, punched past point, again a bit of fumble there.  Dwayne Smith the culprit.
keeper goes back for Dravid. On the middle and leg, whipped to long leg
Boom! Full and well outside off stump, Tendulkar leans forward and thumps it down the ground. Bradshaw looks disappointed with his delivery. Shake of head and walks back
reverts to length but the line is still well outside off, cut to deep point
again slanting away, again bit of width outside off, dabbed to third man
on the leg stump line, tries to work it to the on side, misses.
back of length, on the off stump, cutting away, punched to point
driven to short midwicket.
on the middle , again slow through the air, swept straight to square leg
slow, on the stumps, no pace no work with, just a tickle to the on side. This is good stuff from Gayle. He has understood the track brilliantly
on the middle and leg, slightly short, whipped past square leg
Tendulkar pulls out his paddle shot, will get a single to the right of short fine leg
goes back, stands tall and punches it to widish long on
outside off, angling away, Dravid shuffles across, then sees the line, gets his bat out, away from his body, pushes it out to extra cover for a single.
offcutter outside off, nudged to back ward point. The partnership is on 49 from 63 balls.
50 of the partnership comes up with a punch to deep cover
slow offcutter, outside off stump, Dravid waits for the ball to arrive, opens the bat-face and runs it down to thirdman.
Tendulkar tries to unsettle the length of Bradshaw. Skips down the track, Bradshaw keeps it outside off and Tendulkar whips it across the line. 200 is up.
singles keep coming. On the off stump, Dravid uses his wrists to send it to the on side and gets an easy single
on the middle, driven to midwicket
on the middle and leg, swept real fine and Marlon Samuels gets across to make the stop. he kicks it near the ropes and they run slow and will only get two.
on the middle, turned to the leg side
fuller and driven down the ground to long on

Tendulkar walks down the track. Gayle keeps it slow through the air, outside off stump, no panic shown at Tendulkar's movement but Sachin is pretty smart as well, uses his wrists, just taps it close to square -leg and will get two runs.
on the middle and leg, worked to square leg
slanting away from the off stump, punched to point
Bosh! Short of length, very slighly mind you, but bit of width outside off and Tendulkar went back and across, waited a touch, allowed the ball to come to him and cuts it behind point.
Whack! bit of unadulterated slog. Back of length, outside the off stump, Tendulkar thrusts his left leg forward and thumps it through midwicket

hattrick four! Tendulkar is running hot here. The best shot of the three. It was full in length, angling away, Tendulkar leant forward, and whipped it from outside off, to the right of mid-on. Pure timing.

Tendulkar takes on Chanderpaul and gets two. Dabbed straight to him at third man, Chanders has his right elbow strapped, can't throw properly,and Tendulkar calls for two. Dravid is all praise for the call. Pats the back of the bat in appreciation.
driven to extra cover, where another fumble results and Tendulkar will retain the strike
on the middle, slow through the air, worked past midwicket
fuller, right up there near the blockhole, in front of middle stump, dug out to the on side
just outside off, strangling line and length, stabbed away to the off side
bit more air this time, driven to long on
on the off and middle, worked past square leg for a single.
outside off, Dravid swats it across, past square leg.
on the legs, Dravid misses an opportunity there, runs off the pads behind square for a single.
superb bit of placement from Tendulkar. Almost walked into the shot, picked it from ouside off and placed it to wide of mid-on and will get two. he is on 48 now.
similar delivery but this time Tendulkar goes with the line, drives to deep cover
Bit of inside edge as Dravid tries to clear mid-on and the ball heads off to wide midwicket region. Four valuabe runs.
change of pace, on the stumps, jabbed away to the on side
another slower one, outside off, Dravid jumps out of the track, cuts it to point
Fifty up! 76th ODI Fifty. Both Dravid and Tendulkar reached their 76th today. Attempted yorker, flicked to long leg
just short of driveable length, outside off stump, pushed to deep point. He leant forward, opened the bat -face and guided it through the gap
Clean strike! Very well placed. Fullish, outside off, Dravid got under the ball, and timed it to left of long-on
attempted yorker, turns into low full toss, driven to Lara at cover. Will get a single though. Runs are beginning to flow.
cut to deep backward point

slower one, on the leg stump line, Dravid is beaten by the change of pace as he tries to force it to the on side, doesn't make contact and the ball rolls off the pads to the off side. They rush across for a quick single.
waist-high full toss, on the stumps, Dravid doesn't time his forcing stroke properly and the ball runs towards long-on
Ah! It was going down the leg side, short of length, slow off cutter, Tendulkar waited for the turn and tapped it fine. Real fine.
fullish, outside off stump, Tendulkar goes down on a bent knee and square drives it imperiously to deep point region. Classy.

almost a mix up. Dravid would have been run out. Emrit fires in a wide throw. Tendulkar turns a delivery on middle and leg to Emrit at short fine leg and is caught ball watching. Dravid almost touches him and then has to rush back. Emrit throw is off the mark.
on the stumps, worked to Bradshaw at midwicket
Dravid backs away to the leg side, throws his bat at a fullish delivery, doesn't time it well and will get a single to long on
Delicate! Full, on the legs, attempted yorker, Tendulkar leans forward, and glances it real fine. Lovely use of the wrists. Powell thought he had a lbw there, is about to appeal!
slower one, turns int o a low full toss, on the off stump, pushed to cover
on the off stump line, Tendulkar pushes it out to deep cover
He gets two of them with a slog stroke. Just threw his bat a fullish delivery, outside off, skies it up but it lands between long off and deep cover
One more run. Low full toss, another heave across the line, but just to right of long on
slow, outside the offstump, Dravid is bit early into his cut and finds the man at deep. If he had waited a touch, he could have placed it better.
floated on the middle and leg stump, attempts to sweep, gloves it over the keeper
deja-vu for Dravid. Like in Chennai, he kept his left foot out and attempted to slog sweep. Ends up sending it down the throat of long on.
turns in from outside off stump, pushes it to cover point and Dhoni will come on strike
on the off stump line, spins in, pushed to the off side
fuller, outside off stump, Dhoni leans forwad to drive to cover
Full, outside off and Tendulkar drives, pleasingly, to long on. The left elbow high and all that jazz.
full and outside off, sliced away to third man. He usually takes a few ball to get his eye in before he tries to go on the offensive
short of length, outside off, punched to deep cover.
fine yorker. right on the off stump line, down comes the bat in a hurry, jabbed away towards mid-off region. Good stuff from Emrit.
overpitched this time, on the middle stump line, whipped to long leg.
chest-high full toss, no-ball called for the height, pulled away to long leg.
sliced away to deep point.
on the middle and leg, worked to long leg. Samuels to Dhoni, Should get interesting
on the off stump, Dhoni shapes for a big heave, changes tack and pushes it to long on
pushed through quicker and fuller, on the leg stump, turned to long leg
Dhoni charges, Samuels tosses it up and it dips. Dhoni arrests his forward movement and prodcues his unique whipping drive, down to long off.
another single, to short fine leg. Lara would be happy with this. Last ball coming up

Drama! Dhoni whips, a bottom-handed twirl of the bat, a fullish delivery high to deep midwicket. Dwayne smith jumps near the ropes and palms it inside the boundary. That was great but while trying to pick the ball up, he ends up flicking it past the ropes! In the end he saved two runs. 4 and not a 6.
edged to third man. will bring Dhoni on strike
Tennis shot to long off. Sort of a forehand down the line and they run hard to come back for two
Wow! What a shot! MSD on LSD! That unique bottom-handed twirl of the bat. Comes down hard on a fullish deliverry and sends it up and over long off. A Dhoni special.
low full toss, pushed to deep square leg
Tendulkar backs outside leg, plays a length-delivery, inside-out to the left of deep cover.
Dhoni goes hard at the delivery again but this time drills it straight to long off. Not happy with the result. Blames the bat and he is off to change the wood.
That one flew over the cuckoo's nest, beyond the trees outside the ground. Dhoni is flying here. Charges down the track and heaves it over deep midwicket.
waist-high full toss, quickish, pulled to long leg
slower, on the off side, Tendulkar rotates the strike back to Dhoni with a push to cover point
on the middle and leg, shovelled to fine leg
Now Tendulkar joins in the fun. Brings back memories of him slog-sweeping Warne and offspinners in his hey day. Goes down on his knee and the white ball soars over deep midwicket. Up UP and over!
Tendulkar retains the strike with a push to midwicket
Tendulkar goes for a paddle sweep , fetches it from outside off, places it to short fine leg

That bottom-handed twirl again. A classic You Tube moment.  Full and right in the slot, the wrists works over time, the bat goes under the ball and sends it flying over long-on. Quite an amazing shot.
fullish, outside off, carved away to right of deep cover.

If Lara had hit, Dhoni would have been a goner. Dhoni charged out, and drilled a fullish delivery to Lara at cover who makes a pretty good stop- that ball was travelling at the speed of light and fires in a throw at non-striker's end, Dhoni had given up but ....

Lara drops a dolly! The cricketing goddess loves irony. AFter the special effort the previous delivery, he drops a simple catch. What's more it runs away to the boundary. Tendulkar had driven uppishly to cover.
Tendulkar walks across to the off stump, tries to tap a ball on the stumps to fine leg, misses and Ramdin gathers.
in the block hole, outside off stump, Dhoni tries to produce his special shot but only ends up squeezing it down the ground. Didn't get the length to get under the ball.
backs away to the leg side, Bradshaw follows him and he scoops it inside out, over cover for 2 runs.

Dwayne Smith drops another dolly. Second life for Sachin. A fullish ball on the legs was whipped away, in the air, to long leg where Smith had all the time to take the catch. Ends up palming it to the boundary.
overpitched on the middle and leg, whipped, along the ground, to long leg. On 97 now.
Wide down the leg side. Bradshaw, from round the stumps, anticpates that Tendulkar might move down the leg side and fires one there but ends up pushing too much down
Tendulkar reaches 99. A slower ball on the stumps was lofted towards long-off. Dhoni set off like a mad bull and turned blind.
Tendulkar reaches his 41st ton with a tickle to midwicket. It was full and going down leg side - it would have been called a wide, Tendulkar reaches out for it and  edges it to midwicket.

inn2.comm: Agarkar starts off with a wide swinging delivery down leg side.
gets his radar right, targets outside off and angling away, left alone
in the zone outside off, Chanderpaul thrusts his right foot across and shoulders arms
And again. Agarkar keeps slanting it away, Chanders keeps leaving em.
gets closer to the off stump, leather meets the wood, as Chanderpaul pushes it to point
slightly short of length, on the middle and leg, whipped to fine leg
fullish, on middle and leg, Gayle plays it across and gets a leading edge to cover where Raina, the substitute fielder, does the job.
on a length, outside off stump, Chanderpaul gets across, dabs it to thirdman for a single
length-delivery whistling through the channel outside off, left alone
leans forward to a length-delivery, outside off, opens the bat-face and runs it past point. Irfan Pathan gets across to make the stop. Cheers from his home ground.
Irfan comes into play again. Huge game for him.
hits the deck short of length, outside off stump, comes in a touch, and Gayle ends up driving outside the line
fuller, on the middle stump line, Gayle leans over, pushes it straight down the ground, Kumble gets across to make a sliding stop.
Just outside off stump, moves away, another one that slides away, left alone. He will bring back one in in an effort to trap Gayle. Watch out for that ball.
lands on middle and off, shapes away a touch, pushed to cover region
banged in short, just outside off stump, Gayle slaps it down to the ground and to point where Yuvraj makes the stop
whoosh! Fullish, outside off and Gayle drives ,in the air, to the right of mid-off. Catch it was the call but it was too wide of the fielder.
on the off stump line, on a length, punched back to the bowler

beauty! Agarkar cleans up Gayle. Peach of a delivery. A perfect off cutter which becomes a classic leg cutter for Gayle. Delivered from slighly round-arm action, it lands on the middle stump, on a length, sucking Gayle tentatively forward before cutting away to crash into the off stump.
short of length, outside off stump, pushed to cover
lands on a length, around off stump, comes in a touch, Chanderpaul gets behind the line, turns it to midwicket.
leans forward, gets solidly behind the line, pushes it out towards mid-off
hits the deck on a length, kicks it up, around off stump line, strangling line and length, defended back down the track
maiden over from Zaheer. On the off stump line, straight, pushed back by Chanderpaul.
Devon Smith is off the mark with a punched-drive past cover. It was fullish and just outside off stump and he played it inside-out. Uthappa does the chasing and produces a neat sliding stop.
lands on the middle and off, goes on with the angle, Smith gets behind the line and offers the full face of the bat in defence
bit of width outside off and Smith crashes it to right of Yuvraj, at point, who gets his  right hand to it to make a half-stop.
full and on the off stump line, driven to Kartik, another substitute, at mid-off
on the off stump line, slanting away, he is yet to bend one back in to the left-hander, pushed to cover
Overpitched on the stumps and Chanderpaul makes him pay with a drive down the ground
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Smith stays back and works it away towards midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump and Smith punches it away towards cover
bit of extra bounce and Smith has to hurry there, awkward looking punch of the back-foot and the ball raced away towards point, yet another diving stop from Yuvraj saves runs
Zaheer pitches it up, probably looking for some swing, ball lands right in the slot outside the off stump and Smith hammers it through extra cover. Excellent timing and placement
defended with a straight bat and the ball rolls back to the bowler
forced away off the back-foot to the cover region
Canders! fuller length delivery outside the off stump, Chanderpaul just walked into the drive and the ball raced away to the long-off fence, excellent hit through the line - all timing
drifting down the leg side and Chanderpaul helps it down to fine leg
punched off the back-foot to the mid-off region, get it just wide of the fielder there and Smith sprits across for a single
pitched up and Chanderpaul drills it straight back and the stumps at the other end cuts off a certain boundary.
good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul cross-bats it towards midwicket, not a well timed shot and the ball rolled away off the inner half of the bat
drifting down the leg side and the ball rolls away off the pad, not sure if there was some bat involved
punched down to mid-on, the fielder is at the edge of the circle and they steal a single
good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul clips it away straight to the square leg umpire, three runs saved
punched off the back-foot and the ball rolls back to the bowler
defended towards short cover and they scamper through for a single
good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul works it away towards square leg

gone! another cross-batted heave and this time the damage is done. Good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpaul plays well and truly across the line, ball hits the bottom half of the bat and balloons up towards deep square leg. Harbhajan moves in from the deep and nicely settles under it. Both the openers are back in the hut and West Indies are in trouble here
yorker lenght delivery, Samules fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad, missing leg and the lbw appeal is turned down
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Samules waits for the ball and works it away towards midwicket
defended straight back down the track
shot! good length delivery outside the off stump. Samules just lines it up and drills it through extra cover - off the mark in style
defended on the back-foot
cut away straight to the fielder at point
forced away towards cover
full and in the slot outside the off stump, probably the slower delivery. Smith just stood his ground and smoked it through covers. Top shot
clipped away off the pads for two more
slightly short and on the middle and leg stump line, Smith jumps into position and clips it away towards backward square, fielder moves across quickly and cuts off the single
short of a good length delivery, cut away off the back-foot and the ball goes straight to Yuvraj at point. Another spectator' catch
worked away well in front of point, Samules is not interested in the single and Smith had to go back. Ganguly hits the striker's end stumps direct but Smith was never in trouble.
good length delivery on the stump, hint of swing and Samules taps it away towards cover
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Samules looking to drive it away on off side ends up with thick inside edge and the ball rolls away towards midwicket
punched away towards point
drifting down the leg side, wrong line - ball clips the pad and trickles down to the fine leg fence - given as runs
good length delivery and Samules hammers it straight to the fielder at mid-off
short ball and Samules pulls it away in the air, up and over the midwicket fielder and the ball screams away to the fence - 8 runs off the over
on a length, on the off stump and punched to cover. As Binoy George, sitting next to me, says no body defends those deliveries, all punched and hit on the up. Cricket has changed big time
on the leg and middle stump line, worked to mid-on
at the stumps, Samuels gets behind to offer the full face of the bat in defence
on the hips, tries to work it to on side, runs off the pads

pushed to mid-on and they set off for a quick run. Kartik, usually a good fielder, rushes in but misses the delivery completely. Zaheer is not happy, and shouts, "cmon Kartik,... haat pey aa raha tha' (it was coming to your hands) Meanwhile Dravid is cramped up a bit, going for the chase. He is off the field now. Sitting behind the lines and getting treatment from the physio. He stretches his left leg and Dravid ouches in pain.
single to mid-on
pushes it across to the off stump, just floats it out there, cut past point and Kumble gets across from thirdman
around the off stump, shapes away a touch, punched to cover
outside off stump, nothing delivery, just floated across, dabbed to thirdman
ambles in, puts one one the middle and leg stump line, punched back to the bowler
fullish and on the leg stump line, tries to tickle it to leg side and it runs off the pads
streaky edge through the vacant slip region. Full and outside off and he drove inside the line
snorter! Surprise bouncer, at the off and middle stump line, Samuels sways away from the line
almost scooped to mid-off. Fullish, he was early into his drive
slow off cutter on the leg stump line, turned to short fine leg
on the off stump line, punched to extra cover where Uthappa makes the stop, threatens to throw but resists.

Wow! what a catch by Yuvraj Singh! The man has to be fit if he can pull this off. And what's more Irfan Pathan gets a wicket. Fullish, on the middle stump line and Devon Smith slogs it across the line and it was flying to left of short midwicket when Yuvraj decided to intervene. He flung himself, both feet in the air, and was almost parallel to the ground when he grabbed the ball. Super effort!
guides his first ball to right of Kumble at thirdman. Kumble fumbles it and Lara comes back for two
this one drifts on to the legs, Lara leans forward, whips it to fine leg
pushed outside off, bit of width and Samuels slices it over cover point. Deliberately guided up and over.

What a tragedy for Lara. This was his last innings in Indian soil and what a sad way to go.  Irfan dropped Samuels but he has taken out Lara, run out at non striker's end. Samuels drove straight at Pathan who palms it straight at the sticks at the non-striker's end and Lara is caught short of the crease. His bat was in the air. Cruel.  I don't really love the cricketing goddess so much now!
on the leg and middle, pushed to short midwicket.
on length, outside the off stump, left all alone
surprise bouncer. He took Samuels by surprise earlier and this time it is Simmons who is stunned. Hops up and then sways away as the ball follows him
Pushes this one down the leg side.
short and wide outside off, slapped past a diving Yuvraj at point
Thwack! Samuels walked across and biffed a fullish delivery over long off. Imperious.
outside off , steered to point

Raina takes out Simmons. Doing his bit to stay in the squad. Samuels steered a off cutter to backward point and set off for a run. Raina swooped in, picked up and hurled a direct hit. Bowden raises the fatal finger. All the drama seems to be happening when Pathan is bowling. A super catch from Yuvraj, a tragic dismissal of Lara and now a direct hit by Raina
in the channel outside off, left alone
on a length, outside off, slanting away, punched to mid-off
full, almost at the blockhole, dug out back to the bowler. his left foot was coming across the line and hence the trouble
low full toss on the middle and leg, driven to long on
floated on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
another slow dipping full toss, on the leg stump line, pushed to midwicket
comes down the track and drives to long on
on a length, outside off stump, pushed to Raina at point. Rather pushed to his right and Raina rushes across.
fullish, well outside off, Samuels reaches out for it and drives, gets a edge and it fllies down to thirdman
on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
slower one on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
beaten! Pitches on a length, on the off stump line and shapes away with the angle, and spits past the outside edge
on the middle stump line, worked to midwicket
flighted outside off, driven to Raina at cover
good delivery, landed on a length, and hastened off the track, Ramdin rushes back and hurriedly defends
floated up, on the middle, driven back to the bowler
outside off stump, driven to cover
tossed up on the middle stump, pushed to mid-on
almost carried to Uthappa at long on. Fullish, outside off and Samuels lofts it towards Uthappa who rushes in and dives forward but can't cusp his palm under the ball
way outside off and Umpire Saheba extends his arms
full in length, slanting away, punched to cover where Raina makes a sliding stop
slower one, full and outside the off stump, Ramdin goes for a wild drive and misses
again bit of width outside off, cut to right of deep point
bit of rubbish delivery. Full and well outside off and Ramdin cleared the bin. Hit it up and over cover
this time wide down the leg stump
on the middle stump line, pushed to the on side
turns in from outside off, Samuels pushes at it, bat and pad together
on the middle stump line, driven to long on
slightly short of length, turns in from outside off,  Ramdin eases back, cuts it through backward point
tossed on the middle, leans forward to drive it to long on
on the middle and leg, Samuels comes down the track and eases it out to long on
lands on a length, just outside off, slants away, punched to deep point
slighty short of length, on the middle and leg stump line, holds its line, jabbed to the off side
slower one, Samuels carves it straight over the bowler and Uthappa gets across in time and palms it inside the ropes
full and on the middle stump line, Samuels is bit late in getting his bat down but manages to do so and keeps it out
on the off and middle, pushed to cover

tickled fine through the vacant slip region. It was on a length, on the middle and off, shaped away, Samuels adjusted to the movement by opening the bat-face and running it down fine. Very well played in the end.
on the off stump line, driven to long on
And again.  The game is meandering a bit
on the middle and leg, pushed to short leg
on the off stump line, steered to point
bit more flight, outside off, driven to deep cover. He leant on to that nicely
in the channel outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
Shot! slightly short and turning away, Ramdin quickly picks up the lenght, leans back and cuts it away well wide of the fielder at gully
quicker delivery and Ramdin is hit on the pad, the slider as they call it. ?Impact was well outside the line of the off stump and the lbw appeal is rightly turned down
forced away towards cover point
bit of air and Ramdin drive it down to long-on
fuller in length and Samuels finds the gap between mid-off and cover
tossed up and turning in, defended watchfully
worked away with the spin to the square leg region, easy single
little nudge down to fine leg and yet another easy single is added to the total but they need boundaries
punched down to mid-off, slight fumble but the batsmen decide not to go for the single
fulltoss on the stump and Samuels tamely punches it back to the bowler, missed out on some easy runs there
worked away off the back-foot to the square leg region
driven off the front-foot but fails to get it past the fielder inside the circle
fuller length delivery, not much turn. Ramdin steps forward and drives it down to mid-off
worked away against the spin and they scamper through for a single
forced away square on the off side, no room for a single there
worked away behind square on the leg side and they cross over for an easy single
driven straight back past the bowler to the long-on region
doosra and Ramdin who was playing for the turn is beaten all ends up - well bowled
driven with a straight bat and they continue to milk single
tossed up and turning in, Samuels comes down the track but fails to get to the pitch of the delivery and in the end defends it down
played away on the leg side, bit of inside edge involved
worked away behind square, another single added to the total
swept away to fine leg
quicker and fuller, jumble of bat and pad. Loud appeal for lbw is turned down and its give as runs. Decent stride in but that looked close
worked away off the back-foot and that's his fifty
turning away a touch, defended on the front-foot
another tight delivery, defended watchfully
fuller and on the pads, driven straight to the fielder a short midwicket
bit too straight and Ramdin drives it down to long-on, easy single to end the over
tossed up and turning in, defended down on the leg side

forced away behind the stumps on the off side and they scamper through for a single, Ganguly moves across quickly and has a go at the striker's end stumps but fails to hit the target, direct hit would have been close
eased way for yet another single
cut away off the back-foot to the third man region, they take on the fielder in the deep and scamper through for the second
swept away fine and the ball races away to the fine leg fence, well played. Minimum effort - Maximum output
on the stumps, Ramdin goes right back and tucks it away towards midwicket

edged and through. quicker delivery outside the off stump, Samules is drawn into the drive and the edge is produced but there is no slip in place and the ball races away to the third man fence. Diving effort in the deep ends in vain

Samules departs. Kumble follows up the quicker delivery with a much slower delivery, Samules is bit early in to the drive, in the end it was more of a chip drive and the ball went straight to the Pathan at long-off. West Indies six down and it's time for drinks
on the leg and middle, Ramdin pushes it away to the on side
topspinner outside off, Ramdin goes back to cut it past point. Lovely shot.
floated on leg and middle, bit too full, worked to deep midwicket
on the middle and leg, turning away, swept to short fine leg
Ramdin sweeps himself out of the game. Tossed up, a touch slower in the air, on the off stump and Ramdin sweeps it straight into Kumble's palms at deep midwicket
pushed that one quicker, outside off and Emrit is struck o nthe pads as he pushes forward.  Harbhajan goes up in appeal, don't know for what. must be sheer boredom.
doosra, just outside off, Emrit leans forward and pushes it away to the off side. Ganguly is at the slips
lands outside off and stays in that region, slightly short, Emrit goes back, steers it to backward point
floated on the middle and leg stump, defended off the front foot
topspinner on the off and middle stump line, pushed away to the on side
outside the off stum, punched to point

Gotcha! trapped him in front. Full in length, lands on the middle stump line and Dwayne Smith goes for a sweep and doesn't make contact. Another one bites the dust as West Indies continue with their meek surrender.
on the middle, goes back to turn it to on side
Yuvraj starts off with a floating delivery outside off stump, slight turn and pushed away to the off side.
lands on a length, goes on straight, defended on the back foot
on the leg stump line, gentle delivery, worked to fine leg
bit of rubbish delivery, well outside off, he tries to cut and doesn't make contact
on the off and middle, leans forward and drives to Agarkar at long on
tucked behind square leg and Kumble rushes in to make the stop.
googly on the leg and middle stump line, is trapped on the pads
on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
on the off stump line, pushed to mid-off
right up there, at the blockhole, on the off and middle, inside edged to the on side.
fires that one full on the middle stump line, pushed back to the off side
loops this one slow and in the air - Kumble is just trying out everything here, played to the off side
outside off, keeps going with the arm, pushed to point
just floated across, on the middle stump line, worked past square leg to Harbhajan Singh
arm ball, comes in from outside the off stump, cut to point
slow through the air, lands on the leg and middle, turns in, bit of edge to the off side
bit of rubbish from both bowler and the batsman. slow, short, outside off, he sort of pulls it, ends up waving it the on side
Cut past point! Line and length begged to be hit and he obliged.
topspinner outside off stump, he goes back and pushes it out to covers
drifting on the legs, worked to midwicket.
huge shout for lbw. Slider on middle and leg, must be going down
on the off stump line, driven to Tendulkar at cover.
slap! Very short and he goes back to pull it past midwicket
pushed that one quicker and flatter outside off, defended off the front foot
edged through vacant slip region. Arm-ball outside the off stump, he goes for a cut and edges it. Looks like Bradshaw has pulled up his shoulder. Play held up.
tossed up, low full toss, worked to midwicket
outside off, worked to behind square leg
the game is drifting a touch here. Everyone seems to be waiting for the curtains to come down.  fullish outside off, edged to short third man
this one is driven to long off
back to the bowler.
banged in short, chest-high, pulled to Harbhajan Singh at deep square leg
full, right up there, pushed to Tendulkar at mid-on. The pain on right shoulder returns for Bradshaw but he continues to bat on
Bradshaw shuffles across, and flicks a delivery from the middle stump line to behind square leg
around the off stump line, driven to cover
swing and a miss. In the zone outside off stump, on a length, Emrit doesn't move his front foot, just has a swing and the ball shaves past outside edge
driven to Ganguly at long on. He fires in a direct hit at the non-striker's end
tossed up, outside off, Bradshaw plays for the spin- Yuvraj rarely turns, only at the top of the run-up, and is beaten
slightly short of length, cut past point
low full toss, comes down the track and drives to long on
wide outside off, left alone
low full toss, outside off, steered to deep point

Uthappa takes a very good catch. Agarkar bangs it short, at the off stump line and Emrit pulls weakly and it looks as if it would drop short of Uthappa at midwicket but he dives forward to take a neat catch
attempts a yorker, outside off stump, stabbed away to the on side
slides that one in with a round-arm action, on the off and middle, defended to the off side
swinging yorker, on the middle stump line, almost beaten, pushes it out to midwicket
Agarkar tries his luck with short pitched stuff again but this time he is pulled to long leg
well outside the off stump, he reaches out for it but can't get to it
on the middle stump line, worked to the on side
drifts on the off stump line, defended to the off side

That's it. India wrap up the series with a comfortable win. Powell attempts to pull a slow delivery from Yuvraj, is too early into the stroke and skies it to for Raina to hold a simple catch at cover.
